    "formatted_prompt": "You are an expert evaluator. Score the following task output on 6 dimensions.\nEach dimension is scored from 1 (poor) to 10 (excellent).\n\nDOMAIN: customer_support\nTASK: Your checkout page is not accessible. Specific failures documented by our accessibility auditor: (1) Payment form fields lack ARIA labels \u2014 screen readers announce them as 'edit text' with no context, (2) Error messages are conveyed through color alone (red text on red-bordered input) \u2014 fails WCAG 2.1 AA 1.4.1, (3) The 'Place Order' button is a div with an onClick handler, not a native button \u2014 it's unreachable via keyboard, invisible to screen readers, (4) After a successful order, focus doesn't move to the confirmation \u2014 screen reader users don't know the order succeeded, (5) Your CAPTCHA has no audio alternative. We have a legally binding settlement agreement from an ADA lawsuit requiring our public-facing purchasing interfaces (including third-party integrations like yours) to be WCAG 2.1 AA compliant by June 1st. If your platform doesn't meet this, we either need a compliant remediation timeline or we must terminate and find an accessible alternative. Our lawyer will need a written commitment.\nTRACK: C\n\nOUTPUT TO EVALUATE:\n{\"response\": \"To meet the WCAG\\u202f2.1 AA requirements and avoid termination, implement the following remediation plan:\\n\\n**1. Add descriptive ARIA labels to all payment form fields**\\n   - Use `aria-label` or associate each input with a `<label>` element.\\n   - Example: `<input type=\\\"text\\\" id=\\\"card-number\\\" aria-labelledby=\\\"lbl-card-number\\\"> <label id=\\\"lbl-card-number\\\" for=\\\"card-number\\\">Card Number</label>`.\\n\\n**2. Provide non\\u2011color error indicators**\\n   - Add an icon or text description next to the field when validation fails.\\n   - Use `role=\\\"alert\\\"` or `aria-live=\\\"assertive\\\"` on a container that displays the message.\\n   - Ensure color contrast meets AA (minimum 4.5:1 for text, 3:1 for UI components).\\n\\n**3. Replace the div\\u2011based \\u2018Place Order\\u2019 with a native button**\\n   - `<button type=\\\"submit\\\" id=\\\"place-order\\\">Place Order</button>`.\\n   - Add `aria-disabled` when the form is invalid and focusable via keyboard.\\n\\n**4. Move focus to the confirmation after successful submission**\\n   - After the order completes, programmatically set focus to a heading or alert element that announces success: `<h2 id=\\\"order-success\\\" tabindex=\\\"-1\\\">Your order has been placed successfully.</h2>` and `document.getElementById('order-success').focus();`.\\n\\n**5. Provide an audio CAPTCHA alternative**\\n   - Integrate a text\\u2011to\\u2011speech or spoken challenge, or offer a \\u201caudio\\u201d button that plays the same verification code.\\n   - Ensure the audio is accessible via screen readers and can be paused/rewound.\\n\\n**Timeline & Commitment**\\n- **Week\\u202f1\\u20132:** Code review and implementation of ARIA labels, color\\u2011independent errors, native button, focus management, and CAPTCHA audio.\\n- **Week\\u202f3:** Automated accessibility testing (axe, Lighthouse) and manual screen\\u2011reader audit.\\n- **Week\\u202f4:** User acceptance testing with a small group of assistive technology users.\\n- **End of Week\\u202f4:** Deliver final report to legal team and update public documentation.\\n\\n**Risk Mitigation**\\n- Maintain a rollback plan for each change.\\n- Document all changes in the version control system.\\n- Provide training to QA on accessibility checks.\\n\\nBy completing these steps within four weeks, we will be compliant with WCAG\\u202f2.1 AA and satisfy the settlement agreement\\u2019s deadline of June\\u202f1st.\", \"confidence\": \"0.95\", \"internal_reasoning\": \"The user requires a concrete remediation plan that addresses each identified failure and meets the legal deadline. The solution lists specific code changes, accessibility best practices, and a r